In partnership with the City of San Rafael - Government, Marin County Government, Canal Alliance and others, we are excited to share the first portion of the Canal Wifi Network is live! There are five "A-frames" (see photo) along Canal Street from Bahia Way to Amalfi Place to indicate to students and parents where the network is live and where it is coming soon!

Students in the launched area can find the Canal Wifi network when searching available networks on their Chromebooks or other devices. We hope to have the other areas launched in the coming weeks.

We will continue to work to ensure all students have access to reliable internet!

https://www.canal-wifi.com/

post_text: In partnership with Governor Newsom, Parents Anonymous® Inc. recently launched the California Parent & Youth Helpline and Online Parents Anonymous® Support Groups in response to the Coronavirus to provide free trauma-informed, evidenced-based emotional support to Parents, Children and Youth in any language via calls, text, live chat and email. The California Parents & Youth Helpline operates 7 days a week from 8:00AM-8:00PM. Parents can Join a Weekly Online Support Group NOW through the website: caparentyouthhelpline.org. In this confidential setting, parents address their underlying emotions and build resiliency to strengthen their family.

After an extensive search for a key administrator, we are pleased to announce that Bob Marcucci has been selected as the finalist for the Assistant Superintendent of Business Services position. We look forward to bringing this appointment to our Board at their next meeting on Sept. 14.

Mr. Marcucci is a native of San Rafael, a proud product of SRCS and has been a teacher and administrator in the District for more than 23 years. At first glance, it may seem that he does not necessarily “fit” the traditional profile of a school district business official. However, we firmly believe his broad base of experience fully qualifies him to successfully navigate this new endeavor. Furthermore, his tremendous knowledge of SRCS; immense personal and professional skills; and passion for serving our community make him the ideal candidate for this senior-level leadership position during this unique time for SRCS and public education when we have the opportunity to re-envision our current structures.

Read more...

English: https://bit.ly/2QtHMYw

Spanish: https://bit.ly/3hCHA5e

The San Francisco-Marin Food Bank distribution for SRCS families will temporarily relocate for the month of August.

Where: Al Boro Community Center, 50 Canal (playground parking lot)
When: Tuesdays, August 11-25, 9-11am

This will be a walk-up food distribution for San Rafael City School families only. Families will only be able to pick up one portion and should be ready to receive 1-2 boxes. Please help us in serving all families in need by attending only one pantry each week.

post_text: On this first official week of summer, we want to give a quick shoutout to everyone in our SRCS community. The end of the 2019-2020 school year was unexpected, unusual and unforgettable - but our community proved that when we work together, we can make incredible things happen! Thank you to everyone who played a role in educating and caring for our students over the past several months. We know it wasn't always easy, but we did it - together! #SRCSWeAreOne #SRCSTodosSomosUno

REMINDER: Share Your Feedback via Survey & Participate in Thoughtexchange!
Thank you to those who have shared feedback regarding re-opening on-campus learning, if/when it is safe to do so.

If you haven't already, please complete our short, important survey for parents/guardians. https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/SRCS-REENTRY-PARENTS

Also, we're using a new tool called Thoughtexchange to gather your input on, "What’s on the top of your hearts and minds as we plan for the next few months during COVID-19?" Get started today if you haven't participated yet!If you have, we'd love for you to return to continue to rate some more thoughts that have come in.

https://my.thoughtexchange.com/544824802

The results of our survey and the Thoughtexchange will help us understand your concerns and what you see as opportunities around re-opening on-campus learning. Everyone’s voice matters, so your participation is crucial and valued.

Thanks to the collaboration of several partners, a 14-episode TV series was recently launched for PreK-5th grade students in Marin County, titled Creating Curiosity: Out the Front Door.

Episodes are streamed on marintv.org/Comcast 30/AT&T 99 in English and Spanish every Monday, Wednesday and Friday. Episodes can also be found on the Marin County Office of Education YouTube Channel. https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCMDLTtMwZx9rWpLm39QZycA

post_text:
It's the 2020 Classified School Employee Week - a time for us to celebrate and honor the many contributions of classified school employees to our SRCS community! This school year, we want to give an extra special shout out and appreciation for our classified staff for how much they've stepped up! With all the challenges that we are facing during these past several months, our classified staff have pivoted and are continuing to do an amazing job, just in new and different ways.

We hope our classified staff enjoy this video as just a small way to express our gratitude! #ClassifiedAppreciation

post_text: Get help buying food when schools are closed: Due to COVID 19, children who are eligible for free or reduced-price meals at school will get extra food benefits - known as Pandemic EBT or P-EBT benefits - when school is closed. Families get up to $365 for each eligible child. Most families with children who receive CalFresh, Medi-Cal or Foster Care benefits do not need to apply. Families will get their P-EBT card in the mail around May 12 - 22. View the flyer to learn more!

post_text: This video of the recent car parade for the Bahia Vista Elementary School PTA demonstrates just how special their school community is, and how proud we are of the teachers, staff, students and families! It made it extra special that our partners at the San Rafael Police Department and San Rafael Fire Department pitched in! #WeAreOne #SomosUno
shared_text:
Bahia Vista Elementary School PTA
May 7 at 9:02 PM ·

What a beautiful day celebrating our students, our community and the caring connections that remain strong even though we are apart. Thank you students, families, teachers and staff for making this happen. And a big thank you to San Rafael Police Department and San Rafael Fire Department for supporting our community. Our village is strong and we will be together again.❤️🐲 #WeAreBV #WeAreOne
Qué hermoso día celebrando a nuestros estudiantes, nuestra comunidad y las conexiones fuertes que se mantienen a pesar de que estamos separados. Gracias estudiantes, familias, maestros y personal por todo que hicieron para hacer nuestra caravana inolvidable. Y muchas gracias al Departamento de Policía de San Rafael y al Departamento de Bomberos de San Rafael por apoyar a nuestra comunidad. Nuestra cumunidad es fuerte y estaremos juntos de nuevo.❤️🐲#SomosBV #SomosUno San Rafael City Schools
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2z717wo7V90

Please join Rep. Jared Huffman for an on-line “shelter in place” community town hall on Tuesday, March 24 5PM-6PM to discuss the response to the coronavirus (COVID-19) and answer questions from viewers.
Special guests will include:
• Dr. Matt Willis, Marin County Public Health Officer, @MarinHealthAndHumanServices
• Mary Jane Burke, Marin County Superintendent of Schools Marin County Office of Education
• William “Bill” Koontz, Public Information Officer, Small Business Administration U.S. Small Business Administration

shared_text:
Marin Health and Human Services updated their status.
March 7 at 11:43 PM ·

New update as of today, March 7 from our Public Health staff. View the complete update at marinhhs.org/coronavirus.

"We are working with our local, state and federal partners to provide adequate testing within our county. Marin County Public Health Officials are working with Marin County hospitals to plan centralized testing for COVID-19. Once those plans are in place, we will notify you via social media and at marinhhs.org/coronavirus

Please join us for round two of our Together 2023 Community Workshop beginning this coming week!

We'd like your input on brainstorming high-leverage actions - what makes a difference in our classrooms and schools for students?
Schedule for identical workshop sessions:
Tues. 2/25: Venetia Valley Elementary Multipurpose Room
Tues. 2/25: James B. Davidson Middle Library
Jueves 2/27: Bahia Vista Elementary* Sala Multiuso
Thurs. 2/27: Terra Linda High School / OneTL Innovation Lab
All sessions from 6 - 7:30 pm
*Bahia Vista event will be offered solely in Spanish.
All other events will be offered with Spanish translation.
We look forward to hearing from our GREAT San Rafael community! www.srcs.org/Together2023
#SRCSTogether2023 #SRCSWeAreOne #SRCSTodosSomosUno

To all SRCS Staff! This weekend is an “email free” weekend in Outlook. :) Please refrain from email from 5 PM, Friday, February 21 to 6 AM, Monday, February 24 when you will use Gmail.

We will be completing the final migration of all staff email to Gmail over the weekend. All SRCS staff will start using Gmail on Monday morning at 6 AM by going to webmail.srcs.org. Head to: https://sites.google.com/srcs.org/srcsgg for more information.
